		<td><b>Re: Dendy clones</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have a loose board with two clock oscillator chips. Since I am using a Dendy-like PAL UMC CPU, I am feeding it 27.000 mhz (roundest clock which is close enough to the original frequency) in a socket for a slight overclock and a NTSC-like clone PPU chip clocked at 21mhz.<br /><br />Works great. Only games that don't like it are the usual NTSC games that give problems on the Dendy. <br />Since I'm with a 60hz PPU instead of the 50hz PPUs Dendy has, extra oddities might apply ...<br /><br />I don't know how games optimized for the Dendy would behave on the weird configuration I built here because I have none to test ... lol<br /><br />(edited for improved readability)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


